cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper proposes a novel architecture and training methodology for facial image deblurring, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The proposed method also involves the use of semantic labels and a segmentation network, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML), respectively. Hence, cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves experiments on different datasets, which could fall under multimedia (MM) and graphics (GR) sub-categories.
